<p class="small-margin-before">Ice Hockey Stick from the legendary Russian Hockey player Sergei Fedorov. He was one of the last Soviet professional hockey players to escape from the USSR in 1990 during his tour to the Goodwill Games in Seattle. After the escape, Fedorov became a part of the infamous “Russian 5” from the Detroit Red Wings NHL club, where he won 3 Stanley cups with this club and had a successful career both in the NHL clubs and in the Russian national team. At the current moment, Sergei continues his professional career in hockey in the management role in CSKA KHL club (Moscow).</p> 
